s and Henri Gaussen's definition, a month is dry when the\nmean monthly precipitation in millimeters is equal to or lower than twice the\nmean monthly temperature in Â°C.\n","linknr":805,"url":"Drought","recorded":1374546751,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Drought&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Drought&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Drought_(disambiguation)","/wiki/File:Drought.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Drought.jpg/170px-Drought.jpg","/wiki/File:Drought.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/Sonoran_desert","/wiki/Mexico","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Precipitation_(meteorology)","/wiki/Ecosystem","/wiki/Agriculture","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Economy","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Cactus","#cite_note-4","/wiki/Mass_migration","/wiki/Horn_of_Africa","/wiki/Sahel","/wiki/Henri_Gaussen","#Consequences","#Globally","#Regions_affected","#Causes","#Types","#Protection_and_relief","#Media","#See_also","#References","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Drought&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/File:Mongolian_Gazelle_dead_of_drought.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Mongolian_Gazelle_dead_of_drought.jpg/170px-Mongo